# Quality gates (Constitution Art. II, X, XI)

## No deferral (Art. XI)
- Fix discovered errors **in the same delivery**. No TODO, no stub, no "follow-up later", no "noted for later" left behind at completion.
- Before calling work done, every item you surfaced is either (a) **resolved inline**, or (b) **converted to a tracked task** in `.memory/project.db` (`task add ...`). Filing a follow-up without the user's explicit OK to defer is forbidden — the default is FIX, not FILE.

## Bug fixes: reproduce-test-first + RCA (Art. II, X)
On any **bug fix**, in order:
1. Write a test that **reproduces the bug** and confirm it FAILS first.
2. Fix the code; confirm the test now PASSES.
3. Include a **`## Root Cause Analysis`** block with at least **five chained "why"** levels from symptom to deepest cause. A symptom-only fix is a violation. If a pattern lets this bug class recur, address it before closing.

## Tests are not optional (Art. II)
- New feature → tests covering the **happy path AND edge cases**. Tests use **real data shapes**, not mocks that don't reflect production.
- TS tests: Vitest + React Testing Library in `app/__tests__/`. Python tests: pytest (+ Polars fixtures) in `ingestion/tests/`.

## Before "done"
Run the verification commands (see `nexus-verification.mdc`) and **fix ALL errors/warnings** — zero `tsc`/`lint`/`ruff` issues. "Just a quick fix" is not an exception (Art. V).
